@Node "Overview" "Action.guide/Overview"
@Next "Requirements"
@Prev "Copyright"
@Toc "Main"

Overview
********

   Action is a program for starting other programs dependent on file
types.  Files are shown, unpacked, executed, etc. dependent on a chosen
action.

   Action executes commands for each passed file appropriate to the
file type, which are described in a file for action definitions.

   For action definitions see @{"Actions" Link "Actions"}.

   WhatIs.library by Sylvain Rougier and Pierre Carette is used to
recognize file types.

   Action is especial suitable for use with ToolManager by Stefan
Becker.


@EndNode

@Node "Requirements" "Action.guide/Requirements"
@Next "Installation"
@Prev "Overview"
@Toc "Main"

Requirements
************

   Action 1.0 needs version 2.04 (37.175) oder higher of the Amiga
Operating System.

   A harddisk is very usefull, but not required.

   Action needs @{b}WhatIs.library@{ub} in @{b}LIBS:@{ub} (included).

   for automatic installation the @{b}Installer@{ub} program is needed.


@EndNode

@Node "Installation" "Action.guide/Installation"
@Next "Usage"
@Prev "Requirements"
@Toc "Main"

Installation
************

   You can easily install Action with the @{b}Installer@{ub} program by running
@{b}Install Action@{ub} from Workbench.

   If @{b}Installer@{ub} is not available, you must copy @{b}libs/WhatIs.library@{ub} to
@{b}LIBS:@{ub}, @{b}S/FileTypes@{ub} to @{b}S:@{ub}, @{b}ENV/Action@{ub} to @{b}ENV:@{ub} and @{b}ENVARC:@{ub}, and the
program @{b}Action@{ub} to a directory in the path manually.


@EndNode

@Node "Usage" "Action.guide/Usage"
@Next "Actions"
@Prev "Installation"
@Toc "Main"

Usage
*****

   @{b}Action@{ub} may be started from Workbench or CLI.

   The command template for CLI usage is:

   @{b}ACTION/A,FILE/A/M@{ub}

@{b}ACTION/A@{ub} is the action to be performed.
@{b}FILE/A/M@{ub} is the list of files,
     for which the action should be performed.  AmigaDOS patterns are
     supported.

   For Workbench usage, @{b}Action@{ub} can be default tool or files can be
passed with shift-double click.

   Action uses two tool types:

@{b}ACTION@{ub} is the action to be performed.
     Default is @{b}View@{ub}.

@{b}WINDOW@{ub} is the window
     for input and output of executed programs.  Predefined is
     @{b}CON:0/21/640/234/Action/CLOSE/AUTO/WAIT@{ub}.


@EndNode

@Node "Actions" "Action.guide/Actions"
@Next "History"
@Prev "Usage"
@Toc "Main"

Actions
*******

   Actions are defined in enviroment variables @{b}ENV:Action/Action.@{i}action@{ui}@{ub}.

   The syntax for action definitions is:

   Lines, which start with @{b}#@{ub}, and empty lines are comments.

   Other lines must start with a file type as used by WhatIs.library.
File types with spaces must be quoted with @{b}"@{ub}.

   These file types are followed by commands to be executed, separated
by spaces or tabs. Multiple commands are separate by commas.

   In commands @{b}%f@{ub} is replaced by the full file name, @{b}%s@{ub} by the file
name without path, @{b}%p@{ub} by the file path and @{b}%t@{ub} by the file type.

   Samples for action definitions are includes for actions @{b}View@{ub} and
@{b}UnPack@{ub} (@{b}env/Action/Action.View@{ub} and @{b}env/Action/Action.UnPack@{ub}).


@EndNode

